Kano Electricity Distribution Company (KEDCO) has said it is energizing existing networks to adequately boost power distribution within the company’s franchise areas. Dr Jamilu Isyaku Gwamna, the Managing Director of KEDCO dropped this hint to journalists on the sidelines of Performance Improvement Plan (PIP) Seminar in Abuja on Tuesday. The seminar which comprises DisCo board members, DisCo top executives and other stakeholders, GenCos, end customers and financial institutions to brainstorm on how to best approach the market, relative to DisCos, is a Capacity-building and Technical Assistance Programme for Nigerian Power Distribution Sector developed by the French Development Agency, supported by the European Union and implemented by Association of Nigerian Electricity Distributors (ANED). In a statement by Ibrahim Sani Shawai, the Head, Corporate Communication Unit, the DisCo’s boss said the firm has already put in place all modalities to improve customer service, ATC and C loss, power distribution and staff welfare. He said the seminar would assist the management in terms of adding to the wealth of network experience that are already in use by KEDCO. He stressed that the many improvement and others still on the way are targeted toward improving the company’s capacity to satisfy its numerous customers in Kano, Katsina and Jigawa States. While lauding its customers for their cooperation, Gwamna said a lot needed to be do in terms of paying their bills so that other basic reforms which the company hopes to implement are not thwarted by lack of funds. 2 yrs after takeover, Kano Disco lags on investments Kano Disco procures 100,000 smart meters page 21 lead business Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin